    "body": "### Problem\n\n`WinSeparator` highlight is not applied when specified in a config file after calling `colorscheme`. This appears to only happen when the terminal has a light background. Perhaps the issue relates to the light/dark background detection and handling.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSet the terminal background to a light color.\n\nCreate an init file, `~/.config/nvim/init.vim`, with the following contents:\n\n```vim\ncolorscheme vim                                                        \nhighlight WinSeparator term=reverse cterm=reverse gui=reverse\n```\n\nRestart nvim and create a vertical split:\n\n```vim\n:vsplit\n```\n\n### Actual and Expected behavior\n\nThe specified highlighting is not applied.\n\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/12a34cac-5561-465e-8e8a-fbb60b44bc1e\" width=\"640\" />\n\nExecuting `:highlight WinSeparator term=reverse cterm=reverse gui=reverse` results in the expected highlighting.\n\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b858405f-5885-43b9-8021-0c6b1920347b\" width=\"640\" />\n\n\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0, v0.10.2, NVIM v0.11.0-dev-1044+g01739d467\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim v9.1does not have the issue when using VertSplit instead of WinSeparator\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.01\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 23.08.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
